Neoglyphic Entertainment, Inc.: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 27, 2017 4:41 AM ET
Software

Company Overview of Neoglyphic Entertainment, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Neoglyphic Entertainment, Inc. operates as a transmedia studio that tells epic stories over multiple mediums worldwide. It offers novel, game, and animated media products; and NeoFur, a plugin that helps developers create short fur, fibers, and other soft fuzzy surfaces for their characters and environments. The company was incorporated in 2014 and is based in Campbell, California.


307 Orchard City DriveSuite 206Campbell, CA 95008United StatesFounded in 2014



Phone: 800-755-8975

www.neoglyphic.com







Key Executives for Neoglyphic Entertainment, Inc.


Neoglyphic Entertainment, Inc. does not have any Key Executives recorded. 



Neoglyphic Entertainment, Inc. Key Developments

Neoglyphic Entertainment Launches NeoFur for Unity
Dec 1 16
Neoglyphic Entertainment announced the release of its 3D graphics technology NeoFur for the Unity game development platform. Previously available only on Unreal Engine 4 and in closed beta for Unity, NeoFur is an easy-to-use, in-editor tool that simplifies the creative process for developers. The tool allows authoring of high quality, fully dynamic fur in real-time. NeoFur enables developers to tackle the creation of often challenging furry and fibrous characters, objects, and soft textures at an authenticity level that has never been achieved in a real-time engine. NeoFur leverages shell-rendering techniques, creating a beautiful illusion of millions of strands of fur. Patent-pending advances have allowed the use of compute shaders and other advanced shading strategies.  The result is fast simulation, realistic physics, and unique level-of-detail systems designed to combat fill-rate, ultimately allowing NeoFur to be authored for Mac, PC and mobile games, VR platforms such as Oculus and HTC Vive, and gaming consoles including Xbox One and PlayStation. NeoFur for Unity's features and performance capabilities include: support for Unity 5.3.5, support for advanced physics and forces, cross platform: PC, Mac, Mobile, VR, & Consoles, demo project with over 30 example materials and assets, one stylized, rigged & animated Sabertooth Tiger asset self-shadowing, physically-based shading support via Unity's Standard Shader, support for morph targets and splines for hair growth and flexible settings to tune for quality and performance. NeoFur's licensing options are aimed at providing access to the technology for individuals, indie studios and AAA studios.


Neoglyphic Entertainment, Inc. Unveils NeoFur 2.0 for Unreal Engine 4
Sep 22 16
Neoglyphic Entertainment, Inc. announced that it has released comprehensive feature updates to its award-winning, cross-platform, real-time fur and fiber technology, NeoFur. Now available, NeoFur 2.0 for Unreal Engine 4 enables developers to better tackle the creation of challenging fuzzy and fibrous characters, objects and surfaces such as furred creatures, carpets, blankets, mosses and other natural landscapes. NeoFur is an easy-to-use, in-editor tool focused on giving developers outstanding performance and a fidelity level never before possible in a real-time engine. The company will provide NeoFur 2.0 as a free upgrade for all existing licensees. NeoFur 2.0's new features and performance improvements include: Global Features: Tutorial videos and over 30 included materials; Motion blur now fully supported; Significantly faster CPU simulation for Mobile, HTML5 and other CPU-only platforms; Support for Nurbs curves via FBX (works w/Maya hair systems); Support for Unreal Engine 4.13; Support for Mac OSX Sierra; Shader features; 4.11 Hair Shading model fully utilized; Per-strand features: size, length, coloring, roughness, scattering; Simulated Undercoat and Overcoat systems; Experimental features: Variable hair clumping via vector maps; Variable hair curling via UV offsets. NeoFur 2.0 creates a beautiful illusion of millions of strands of fur, now with realistic anisotropic reflections, light scattering and shadowing. Neoglyphic's advances have allowed the use of compute shaders and other advanced shading strategies to take that technique to the next level, bringing fast simulation, realistic physics, and unique Level-Of-Detail systems designed to combat fill-rate.


Neoglyphic Entertainment Expands Visionary Sunborn Rising Fantasy Series with New Mobile Game, Endless Rush
Aug 18 16
Neoglyphic Entertainment announced the availability of Endless Rush, a visually stunning endless runner mobile game. The new mobile game brings to life the story of the company's debut fantasy novel and immersive reading app, Sunborn Rising: Beneath the Fall. In the first cross-medium implementation of its kind, players earn digital currency in the Endless Rush game that unlock deeper story elements in the Sunborn Rising immersive reading app and vice versa. By leveraging its proprietary platform technology to build a better form of storytelling, the Sunborn Rising franchise, including Endless Rush, delivers engaging entertainment experiences across multiple mediums for deeper audience involvement in an incredible story. Now available in the Apple App Store, Endless Rush places fans of the franchise returning and new into the 3D world of Cerulean as imagined by Sunborn Rising's author, Aaron Safronoff, and its acclaimed artist and chief creative officer, Christopher Chamberlain. The game tasks players with collecting power ups and nectar all while zooming through lush canopies and botanical obstacles as an adorable, furry, six-winged dynamo creature from the book. The true magic of the franchise is in the connectivity between the Endless Rush mobile game and the Sunborn Rising immersive reading app. By allowing readers, and players, to simultaneous engage with both formats including quick-paced action in Cerulean's forest, art and original music they can immerse themselves in Barra's world in the most complete way. First Cross Platform Integration for Reader Story Development; As players progress through Endless Rush, digital currency is earned and can be used to unlock the full experience of the immersive novel. Additional currency can be earned by finding hidden items while reading Sunborn Rising: Beneath the Fall, or downloading it through the mobile game and vice versa. The Sunborn Rising: Beneath the Fall novel, immersive reading app and Endless Rush were created using Neoglyphic's advanced data-science publishing platform, which helps publishers find great stories, match them to appropriate market segments and enable complimentary entertainment experiences to be built for all audiences and demographics, including reading apps, games, virtual reality and more. Beginning August 20, 2016, Neoglyphic celebrates the game and immersive novel release by offering a site-wide 50-75% off promotional sale on all Sunborn Rising experiences and merchandise. The Sunborn Rising promotion ends August 24, 2016.


